description:
The following traits have been repeatedly observed and are determined to be unique characteristics of ‘Stream’ which in combination distinguish this Vriesea as a new and distinct cultivar:



        1. Funnel form rosette plant, measuring about 45 cm in height and 35 cm to 45 cm in diameter;
        2. Compound, red, bipinate spike inflorescence, measuring about 16 cm to 26 cm in height;
        3. About 2 to 8 branches, measuring about 10 cm to 16 cm in length and about 3.5 cm to 5.5 cm in width; and
        4. Medium green foliage, measuring 15 cm to 25 cm in length and 4.5 cm to 5.0 cm in width.
